---
"watsonx-ai-provider": major
---

v2.0.0 — Major rewrite. Targets Vercel AI SDK v6, drops the `@ibm-cloud/watsonx-ai` SDK in favor of direct REST calls, and aligns the implementation with the canonical Mistral provider in the AI SDK.

### Breaking changes

- **Vercel AI SDK v6 required** (was v4 in v1.x). Listed as a peer dependency `ai ^6.0.0`.
- **`@ibm-cloud/watsonx-ai` SDK no longer a dependency.** The provider hits `/ml/v1/text/chat`, `/ml/v1/text/chat_stream`, and `/ml/v1/text/embeddings` directly via `postJsonToApi` from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`.
- **IAM-only authentication.** `WATSONX_AI_AUTH_TYPE` is no longer read. v2 supports only IAM via `WATSONX_AI_APIKEY`. Bearer / Basic / CP4D auth modes are gone.
- **`LanguageModelV3` specification.** v1.x implemented `LanguageModelV2`. The constructor and call shape both change accordingly.
- **Constructor signature changed**: `new WatsonxChatLanguageModel(modelId, settings, config)` → `new WatsonxChatLanguageModel(modelId, config)`. The `settings` argument is gone.
- **`WatsonxChatSettings` type removed.** Standard generation parameters (`temperature`, `topP`, `topK`, `maxOutputTokens`, `stopSequences`) now flow through `LanguageModelV3CallOptions` on each call. wx.ai-specific knobs live under `providerOptions.watsonx` (parsed via the new `watsonxLanguageModelOptions` zod schema).
- **`provider` strings now differentiated**: chat models report `'watsonx.chat'`, embedding models report `'watsonx.embedding'` (was `'watsonx'` for both).
- **`DEFAULT_MAX_TOKENS` constant removed.** `maxOutputTokens` is passed through verbatim — wx.ai's server default applies when the caller omits it. v1 silently capped at 1024.
- **`zod` peer dependency tightened to `^4.0.0`** (was effectively bundled with the old `@ibm-cloud/watsonx-ai` chain in v1). v2 uses zod v4-only API (`.loose()`).
- **Node engines bumped to `>=20.3.0`.** Required for `AbortSignal.any` used in the stall watchdog.
- **Empty user-message file parts now throw `UnsupportedFunctionalityError`** instead of being silently dropped. wx.ai chat only supports image file parts.
- **`createWatsonxProvider` deprecated** in favor of `createWatsonx`. Alias is still exported for back-compat; it's the same function.

### Added

- **Direct streaming via `doStream`** using `postJsonToApi` + `createEventSourceResponseHandler` + a `TransformStream`. Replaces v1's wrapper around the IBM SDK. Adds zod-validated chunks, retry support, response-size guard, multi-byte UTF-8 framing, standard error shape.
- **Vision / image input support** for compatible models. Vision models now also accept https image URLs directly via `image/*` allowlist on `supportedUrls` (v1 forced data-URL conversion).
- **Embedding models** via `provider.embeddingModel(...)` and the deprecated-alias `provider.textEmbeddingModel(...)`. Includes preflight `TooManyEmbeddingValuesForCallError` for batches over 100.
- **IAM token caching** with automatic refresh and 401-retry. In-flight token requests for the same API key are deduplicated.
- **`providerOptions.watsonx`** options:
  - `timeLimit` — server-side wall-clock cap (ms)
  - `parallelToolCalls` — controls concurrent tool calls
  - `reasoningEffort` — `'low'` / `'medium'` / `'high'` for reasoning-capable models. Forwarded to wx.ai as `reasoning_effort`. Verified on `openai/gpt-oss-120b` (HIGH produces ~3× the reasoning of LOW). Models without reasoning capability accept the field but produce no `reasoning_content`.
- **Custom `fetch` injection** via `WatsonxProviderSettings.fetch` for testing, middleware, proxying.
- **Custom `generateId` injection** via `WatsonxProviderSettings.generateId` for deterministic test IDs.
- **Default `watsonx` instance** exported — `import { watsonx } from 'watsonx-ai-provider'` reads `WATSONX_AI_APIKEY` / `WATSONX_AI_PROJECT_ID` automatically.
- **`responseFormat`** support — JSON mode (`type: 'json_object'`) and JSON schema (`type: 'json_schema'`).
- **`includeRawChunks`** call option honored — emits `{ type: 'raw' }` stream parts when set.
- **`tool.strict`** flag forwarded to wx.ai when present on function tools.
- **User-agent suffix** `ai-sdk/watsonx/${VERSION}` on outbound requests for IBM-side telemetry attribution.
- **Stream anomaly diagnostics**:
  - Always-on warning when wx.ai bills `completion_tokens > 0` but never streams content (known mistral-medium-2505 bug fingerprint).
  - Opt-in raw-chunk trace via `WATSONX_DEBUG_STREAM=1` env var for IBM bug reports.
- **Full `ProviderV3` interface**: `specificationVersion = 'v3'`, `imageModel(...)` stub that throws `NoSuchModelError`, `embeddingModel(...)` (alongside the existing deprecated `textEmbeddingModel`).
- **`response-metadata` stream part** emitted on the first chunk of every stream.
- **TypeScript strict mode** enabled in build.
- **ESM + CommonJS dual module output** with full type declarations for both.
- **Comprehensive unit test suite** (Vitest) and e2e test harness against live wx.ai.
- **Build-time version injection** via tsup `define`; `VERSION` constant always reflects the published `package.json` version.

### Changed

- **`doGenerate` and `doStream` use `combineHeaders`** so caller `options.headers` are merged correctly with provider headers and auth.
- **`getResponseMetadata()`** extracted as a helper, used by both `doGenerate` and `doStream`.
- **`prepareWatsonxTools()`** extracted to its own file.
- **`parseToolCallArgs`** unwrap behavior gated to `ibm/granite*` models only — won't mutate well-formed tool args from other providers.
- **`response.body`** in `doGenerate` and `doEmbed` results now contains the raw wire payload (`rawValue`), not the zod-validated object — preserves fields the schema strips for telemetry consumers.
- **`WATSONX_API_VERSION` bumped from `2024-10-08` to `2026-04-20`** (matches the value shipped in `ibm-watsonx-ai` Python SDK 1.5.10). The previous date was ~18 months stale.
- **Stream IDs** use `generateId()` from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils` instead of `Date.now()` (no millisecond collisions across concurrent streams).
- **`AbortSignal` composition** for stall watchdog uses `AbortSignal.any` cleanly composed with caller's signal (no parallel `Promise.race` machinery).
- **`watsonxErrorSchema`** normalizes `statusCode` and `status_code` into a single `statusCode` field via `.transform()`.

### Fixed

- **gpt-oss tool-call finish reason** — gpt-oss models report `finish_reason: 'stop'` instead of `'tool_calls'` when returning tool calls; the provider now overrides this when tool calls are present.
- **`mistralai/pixtral-12b`** typo (was `pixtrail-12b` in earlier work).
- **`options.headers`** now forwarded on chat paths (previously only embedding model honored them).
- **Tool-call delta `tool-input-start`** now emitted exactly once per tool-call (previously re-fired on every delta carrying `function.name`).
- **`convertUsage`** is null-safe — wx.ai responses without a usage block no longer throw.

### Known limitation

- **`mistralai/mistral-medium-2505`** + tool calling has a wx.ai-side streaming bug: the model generates tokens (billed) but never transmits them via SSE deltas. Affects streaming only; non-streaming `generateText` works. The anomaly warning fires automatically when this is observed. Use `openai/gpt-oss-120b`, `meta-llama/llama-3-3-70b-instruct`, or `ibm/granite-4-h-small` for streaming tool-call workloads. Re-tested under API version `2026-04-20` and the new doStream pipeline; bug confirmed wx.ai-side, not version- or implementation-related.
